    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>Oct 16. 5611</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yesterday I recd yours <date>7th</date> inst, and<lb/> I hasten to
                reply in order to give you advice<lb/> which you will just heal as you please, and I
                shall<lb/> not feel hurt however much my counsel may<lb/> be disregarded. I only
                feel warranted in this cause<lb/> from the fact that you have seen fit to send<lb/>
                <sic>proff</sic> sheets of the article in question to me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I think by publishing it, you will<lb/> gain nothing in the eyes of
                your friends,<lb/> whilst you will afford your enemies matter<lb/> to be handled by
                them in <del>to</del> trying to prove your<lb/> bitterness of feeling, with which at
                times<lb/> they have charged you, however unwarranted,<lb/> in so doing.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If anything of the kind is to appear<lb/> at all it would be better
                to emanate<lb/> from a third party and to be published<lb/> in some other sheet than
                the Occident<lb/> But I candidly think your remarks<lb/> in last months Occident are
                all you<lb/> need make in the premises.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It might not be out of the way<lb/> for you to send similar proof
                sheets<lb/> to those sent me to a few friends<lb/> in the principal cities of the
                union<lb/> and let them show them to your<lb/> particular friends stating that
                you</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>did intend to publish but was<lb/> urged by true friends to omit<lb/> doing so.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I would remark that<lb/> both <persName>Mr. Touro</persName> and
                    <persName>Mr Gutheim</persName><lb/> are of opinion that you would<lb/> do
                better in not publishing<lb/> the document &amp; object to my idea of sending it to
                your particular friends in proof sheet form. <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> I<lb/>
                may see to day and will ask<lb/> his views which if they be<lb/> different to ours I
                will at<lb/> once communicate to you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have only a short<lb/> time left before the mail<lb/> closes,
                    <del>but</del> and would not<lb/> write till the last moment<lb/> in order to
                gain as much time<lb/> as possible to think in this matter</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">All that you ask for in<lb/> your letter from me I have<lb/> sent
                some days ago. I think<lb/> on the <date>2d.</date> Inst &amp; which you recd.<lb/>
                a few days after lastly addressing<lb/> me.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose Second of Ex, First of<lb/> which was forwarded in mine of
                    <date>2d.</date><lb/> inst. Remember me to my dear Aunt and<lb/> be assured of
                the <sic>unchangable</sic> friendship of</p>
            <p>yours Truly</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Gershom K</persName>
            </p>
            <p
                rend="The following part of the sentence in the text above on page 2 appears on page 3"
                >particular friends in proof sheet form.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p><persName>Mr Touro</persName> recd a letter from you<lb/> also yesterday he desired
                me to acknow<lb/>ledge it sends his best respects and<lb/> will reply soon</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penna</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
